title: One of TWO High Grade Trap Shotguns
postcontent:
Custom built Browning BT-99 Single barrel Trap
Re-stocked in extremely rare Bastogne Walnut with 28 lines per inch hand checquering.  Bastogne Walnut is an extremely rare cross between California Claro and English Walnut.  It is a much denser wood than either of the parent trees. The color contrasts are of the brilliant Claro with the dark lines of English Walnut.  The blank from which the stock and forend were cut costs $340 over 20 years ago!  The stock was created by Jim Collinger, famed Mid-west stock maker.  It has two degrees cast off to fit snugly beneath the eye.  Bore has been back bored to relieve pressure of the shot charge and the forcing cone has been removed and polished out.  The barrel was sent to Herb Orr, world famous choke man and his "Sweet 16" choke was installed.  This Orr choke will place 92% of one and one-eight ounce of #8 shot within a 30" circle at 32 yards.  A Tillotson Pull/Release Olympic trigger has been installed and the gun can be shot either way by releasing the trigger on the swing or the normal pulling of the trigger.  This is truly a one-of-a-kind trap shotgun!  Too ashamed to tell you what I have invested in this gun!  Selling for health reasons. $750.00
